title: As not unknowne. This petition or prophecie on record, presented to His Majestie in the yeare 1633. Alongtime though hath waited, yet be it knowne was accomplished, then this present year: 1644. When He on a Friday morning was killed or suffered....
author: Eleanor, Lady, d. 1652. To the Kings most excellent majestie. The humble petition of the Lady Eleanor. 1633.
